{
  "text": "For the matched cohort study, patients with severe sepsis suffering IFI during their ICU stay were matched to control patients with severe sepsis but without IFI. We attempted to match each individual with severe sepsis with a control patient in the same center. The matching process included the following factors: sex, age (± 10 years) and APACHE II score (± 3) [CITATION_1] . If one patient could be matched to two or more control patients, then the control patient with the closest APACHE II score was selected.",
